latestIgtvVideos.title: Joint mobility series for beginners!
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
View and save this if you want to start yoga and it’s your very first time. .
.
The ideal way to start is by first priming your joints in place of jumping straight on to asanas. I still practice it daily before I do any asanas. Starting right will take you long and give you the right results and benefits. .
.
The series comprises of movement of every single joint in the body. This is the first part of the series and there are more to joint mobility. .
.
Whether you are a new mom just willing to start yoga post baby or you are recovering from any problem, this is the safest for all to practice. .
.
Approved for people with joint pain, stiffness, any kind of mobility issues. .
.
You can do it on the bed too, if you have trouble sitting on the mat on the floor. How easier can it be! .
.
If you think the video is fast paced and you can’t catch up, feel free to DM or drop in comments. We can do a live session too🌺
.
.
Start today, practice daily, stay safe!

Frozen Dates & Peanut Butter Bites 

Ingredients:
Medjool dates – 10 (pitted)
Peanut butter – 5–6 tbsp (creamy or crunchy, your call)
Crushed pistachios – 2–3 tbsp
Sea salt – a pinch (optional, but highly recommended)

Instructions:
✨Prep the Dates
 Slice each date open lengthwise (not all the way through) and remove the pit, if needed.

✨Stuff Them
 Fill each date with about 1/2 tbsp of peanut butter. Gently press them closed.

✨Top It Off
 Drizzle with crushed, salted pistachios for that perfect nutty crunch.

✨Freeze
 Place the stuffed dates on a parchment-lined tray and freeze for 20–30 minutes, until firm.

✨Serve
 Enjoy straight from the freezer — chewy, nutty, crunchy, creamy bliss in every bite!
